China is compelling Tibetan herders to settle in towns for development, depriving them of their traditional way of life.
Land confiscation and evictions are common, with minimal compensation.
The government cites overgrazing as the reason for these changes.
The relocation program aims to combat desertification, a widespread issue in China.
Guizhou Province is particularly affected by stone desertification, threatening the livelihood of farmers.
Efforts to reverse soil erosion have been successful in some areas, but urbanization and industrialization pose challenges.
Xinjiang is also grappling with soil erosion, exacerbated by human activities and natural factors.
